# üêû bug report
### Affected package
@angular/core
### Description
When i try to extends built-in Angular decorator ```Component```, application was crashed with error: ```Failed to load my.component.html (404 Not Found)```.

Here is my code of decorator:
```
export function MyComponent(cfg: Component): TypeDecorator {
  const decorator = Component(cfg);
  return function (cls: Type<any>) {
    return decorator(cls);
  };
}
```
Here's its usage:
```
@MyComponent({
  selector: 'app-my-component',
  templateUrl: './my.component.html',
  styleUrls: ['./my.component.scss'],
})
export class MyComponent {
}
```

I found out that if you use the standard ```Component``` decorator, then meta.templateUrl will resolve in meta.template. But if i use custom directive, nothing happend. Application trying to get ```my.component.html``` from ```http://localhost/my.component.html``` by xhr request, and crashed when receive error 404.

Why this happens I do not understand, most likely it is a bug.

Here is my dependencies: 
```        "@angular/animations": "^7.2.7",
